[http://archlinuxarm.org/platforms/armv5/seagate-goflex-net ''Run Linux on the GoFlex Net'']
===Specifications=== *Processor: [[Marvell]] Kirkwood @1.2GHz :Architecture: ARMv5te *RAM: 128MB (DDR2-800) *Flash: 256MB (NAND) *USB: 1x USB 2.0 *SATA: 2x SATA *LAN: 1x GbE (RJ45) <small> :The GoFlex Net is a device based on the [[Marvell]] Sheeva plug computer ::platform, and is the successor to the [[Seagate Dockstar]]. :Unlike the [[Seagate Dockstar|DockStar]], this device has two SATA ports that are externally ::accessible for the GoFlex range of portable hard drives. :These are standard SATA ports so any bare 2.5" drive can dock in there, but ::a snug and secure fit will only be achieved by using the GoFlex drives.
:There are nine total LEDs accessible: a dual color orange/green LED, and two banks ::of four white LEDs that were originally used as indicators for drive space usage. </small>
